text=https://i.imgur.com/q4y8vkR.jpg%0a(:include GameRef.Directorycity:)%0a(:div %25width=100%25 style='color:white;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:fixed;background-color:black;background-position:bottom center;background-image:url([=https://i.imgur.com/Eboteal.png=]); background-size:100; padding:25px;' width=100%25:)%0a%0a!%25center%25%25color=#008080%25'''Society of the Cinders'''%0a%0a%25center%25%25color=#008080%25''(Open Membership for levels 1–3. For levels 4 & 5 members must be a veteran of the War of Four)'' \\%0a%0a(:table valign=top:)%0a(:table table border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0:)%0a(:cellnr width=200 align=center:)''' %25color=#008080%25 MCI Name:'''%0a(:cell width=400:) Society of the Cinders%0a(:cellnr width=200 align=center:)''' %25color=#008080%25 Territory:'''%0a(:cell width=400:) Empty%0a(:cellnr width=200 align=center:)''' %25color=#008080%25 Goal:'''%0a(:cell width=400:) Empty%0a(:cellnr width=200 align=center:)''' %25color=#008080%25 Merits:'''%0a(:cell width=400:) Empty%0a(:cellnr width=200 align=center:)''' %25color=#008080%25 Theme:'''%0a(:cell width=400:) Empty%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a(:table table border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0:)%0a%0a! %25center%25%25color=#008080%25MCI Members%0a%0a||! Image ||! Name ||! MCI Status ||! Venue ||! Type ||%0a|| %25thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/6erVy2R.png || %25color=#008080%25Empty || Leader || Empty || Empty ||%0a|| %25thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/6erVy2R.png || %25color=#008080%25Empty || Second || Empty || Empty ||%0a|| %25thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/6erVy2R.png || %25color=#008080%25Empty  || Member || Empty || Empty ||%0a|| %25thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/6erVy2R.png || %25color=#008080%25Empty  || Member || Empty || Empty ||%0a|| %25thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/6erVy2R.png || %25color=#008080%25Empty  || Member || Empty || Empty ||%0a|| %25thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/6erVy2R.png || %25color=#008080%25Empty  || Member || Empty || Empty ||%0a%0a%0a!!!%25center%25'''%25color=#008080%25Intro''' \\%0a%0a%25center%25''“You cannot qualify war in harsher terms than I will. War is cruelty, and you cannot refine it; and those who brought war into our country deserve all the curses and maledictions a people can pour out. I know I had no hand in making this war, and I know I will make more sacrifices to-day than any of you to secure peace. […] But these comparisons are idle. I want peace, and believe it can only be reached through union and war, and I will ever conduct war with a view to perfect an early success.”'' [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25center%25- '''William Sherman''' -%0a%0aDuring the War of Four Factions, sin burned liked flame, condemning many a good person to ash and to dust. The Society of the Cinders caters to those diamonds the rough, survivors and sycophants that lasted through the flame. Officially, the Society of Cinders is a social club dedicated to advocating for the rights of Veterans of Four Factions and offering support to all Veterans. They gained a reputation from stopping a series of executions that were thinly veiled attempts to settle old grudges.%0a%0aNot all veterans, even among those who receive services, are actual members. However, the cult claims to represent all veterans regardless of their actual membership. The cult wraps itself in the narrative of the war and wears its scar like a fine suit. The Society of the Cinders takes it upon itself to deal with the lingering monstrosities from the war. They also simultaneously serve as a living, gruesome reminder for what transpired there, a reminder for why this peace is necessary, and as a gatekeeper against the worst stories.%0a%0a%0a!!!%25center%25'''%25color=#008080%25Purpose''' \\%0a%0aNever forget the war and what happened there, so that it might never happen again. Never forget those who sacrificed so that it ended. Never forget that there are monsters out there who would weave the sins of the past into an atrocity for the future.%0a%0a!!!%25center%25'''%25color=#008080%25Doctrine''' \\%0a%0aThe cult is a meritocracy ruled by consensus. It’s a network of social ties built on respect and shared trauma, bundled together and given direction by a few people. War stories and veteran rights are the only doctrine, though secretly the cult takes a keen ear to who should be sharing what story.%0a%0a%0a!!!%25center%25'''%25color=#008080%25Relic''' \\%0a%0aA simple urn that contains ashes from those lost in the war. The urn contains the ashes from all five factions, and despite its small size is said to contain the ashes from hundreds or thousands of soldiers. Those in the cult who die, even if they were not veterans of the war, have the option of being cremated and having their ashes placed in the urn, along with a memorial that tells of their exploits.%0a%0a%0a!!!%25center%25'''%25color=#008080%25Titles and Mechanics''' \\%0a%0a||! Status Level ||! Title ||! Benefits ||%0a|| • || Level || You can tell yourself that you haven’t joined a cult—you’re just a Drinking Buddy who likes to hear stories. You’ve started to frequent places where Veterans from the War of Four Factions tend to visit, and they know you. You gain Contacts • (War of Four Veterans) representing the stories they are willing to tell you about the past and the present. All you have to do is listen and appreciate. ||%0a|| •• || Level || Advocates are told the troubles that Veterans from the War of Four Factions have and are expected to respond favorably. Veterans know who has their back, and in turn they have yours. You gain Allies • (War of Four Veterans). ||%0a|| ••• || Level || Those who delve into the secrets and atrocities of the past and wear those scars proudly are call Heroes, often in mockery of the villainy they performed. Gain the Air of Menace or Empath merit, depending on whether you carry those scars with you or help others face them. ||%0a|| •••• || Level || Correspondents graduate from responding to the needs of Veterans to anticipating when politics will turn against them and proactively mobilizing other members of the cult. Each faction gets their information from a different source. Changelings and Mages peer into dreams, gaining Dream •••. Mortals and Werewolves rely on their interpersonal connections and quid-pro-quo, gaining three dots of Contacts. Vampires read the secret signs scattered around the city and the political climate from afar, gaining Cacophony Savvy •••. ||%0a|| ••••• || Level || Some cults become Legends in their own time, iconic names whose stories are uttered in the same breath as the war itself. These are either people who lived and fought during the war, or have made such great strides for veterans that their name is synonymous with protecting them. They learn to cultivate a mystique of desperation and insanity, while toeing the line between “crazy” and “too crazy,” and few will harm another veteran while in their presence. All members at this level receive Fame • related to their past service or their current efforts as well as Jack-Booted Thug. Jack-Booted Thug applies applies to all Veterans of the War of Four Factions and all members of the Society of the Cinders instead of Carthians. The user may use their Mystery Cult Initiation in place of City Status, while onlookers may use any supernatural status in place of their City Status. ||%0a%0a%0a!!%25center%25%25color=#008080%25'''Deeds'''%0a%0a*Example%0a*Example%0a*Example%0a*Example%0a*Example%0a*Example%0a%0a%0a!!%25center%25'''%25color=#008080%25Contact''' \\%0a%0a%25center%25SoulGambit%0a%0a%0a(:table table border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0:)%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a!%25center%25%25color=#008080%25'''Quotes'''%0a%0a%25mortal%25 ''"I am a quote! Fear me!"'' -'''A person with a face'''. \\%0a%25mage%25 ''"I am a quote! Fear me!"'' -'''A magic person'''. \\%0a%25vampire%25 ''"I am a quote! Fear me!"'' -'''A person with fangs'''. \\%0a%25werewolf%25 ''"I am a quote! Fear me!"'' -'''A person that can woof'''. \\%0a%25changeling%25 ''"I am a quote! Fear me!"'' -'''A person that is lost'''. \\%0a%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a%0a%0a!! %25center%25%25color=#008080%25 Color Codes%0a%0aUse the below codes to change your color to one you want! you can either do it by using the word or the hashtag and number code.%0a%0a%25werewolf%25 Werewolf [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25mage%25 Mage [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25vampire%25 Vampire [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25changeling%25 Changeling [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25mortal%25 Mortal [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=hardblue     color=#0000cc%25 hard blue [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=darkgreen    color=#006400%25 dark green [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=bluegrass    color=#009999%25 blue grass [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=teal         color=#008080%25 teal [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=darkpurple   color=#660066%25 dark purple [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=perwinkle    color=#6600cc%25 periwinkle [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=darkgrey     color=#a9a9a9%25 dark grey [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=mistgreen    color=#669966%25 mist green [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=slategreen   color=#669999%25 slate green [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=lightpurple  color=#9966cc%25 light purple [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=lightgrey    color=#999999%25 light grey [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=lightblue    color=#add8e6%25 light blue [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=springgreen  color=#00ff7f%25 spring green [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=magenta      color=#ff00ff%25 magenta [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=burntorange  color=#cc6633%25 burnt orange [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=grey         color=#808080%25 grey [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=lightgreen   color=#90ee90%25 light green [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=pink         color=#ffc0cb%25 pink [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=lightred     color=#ff6666%25 light red [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=orange       color=#ffa500%25 orange [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=lightorange  color=#ff9966%25 light orange [[%3c%3c]]%0a%25define=gold         color=#ffd700%25 gold [[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a(:include GameRef.Directoryhelp:)
